main event: Two air traffic controllers at Bismarck Airport in North Dakota observed two moving star-like light sources in the sky on November 26, 1968.
interesting points: One light was traveling north and the other was traveling south, with the southern light disappearing in the northeast.
The witnesses described the lights as bright, solid, and round, about the size of a bright star.
The lights moved considerably faster than normal aircraft and made unusual maneuvers, including a 90-degree turn.
The Air Force was alerted to the incident, and there had been previous reports from citizens in the area of strange objects in the sky around the same time of night.
The witnesses considered natural phenomena like ball lightning but ultimately could not identify the objects.
sighted object: two bright, solid, round light sources
